<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="363" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,836,1259]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,945,971]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Remarks:</emphasis>
having been instituted as a geographic race, we rank it subspecific, and thus available (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[1298,1432,945,971]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 10, glossary). 
<bibRefCitation author="Hubendick, B." box="[361,566,980,1007]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="1 - 223" refId="ref17396" refString="Hubendick, B. (1951) Recent Lymnaeidae. Their variation, morphology, taxonomy, nomenclature, and distribution. Kongliga Svenska vetenskaps-akademiens Handlingar, Stockholm. Fjarde Serien, 3 (I), 1 - 223." type="journal article" year="1951">Hubendick (1951)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Alzona, C." box="[619,782,981,1007]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="1 - 433" refId="ref15337" refString="Alzona, C. (1971) Malacofauna Italica. Catalogo e bibliografia dei molluschi viventi, terrestri e d'acqua dolce. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali e del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Milano, 111, 1 - 433." type="journal article" year="1971">Alzona (1971)</bibRefCitation>
listed “ 
<emphasis box="[869,1003,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">neapolitana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[1010,1158,981,1007]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="33 - 44" refId="ref15711" refString="Bellini, R. (1904 d) The freshwater shells of Naples and the neighbourhood. Journal of Conchology, 11 (2), 33 - 44." type="journal article" year="1904">Bellini, 1904</bibRefCitation>
” as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Muller, 1774)" authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1774" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1774" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Galba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hygrophila" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="truncatula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Galba truncatula</emphasis>
(Müller, 1774)
</taxonomicName>
, and the same holds for 
<bibRefCitation author="Fasulo, G." box="[713,871,1017,1043]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="1 - 3" refId="ref17022" refString="Fasulo, G. (2013) Molluschi extramarini (terrestri e dulciacquicoli) &quot; campani &quot; per toponimia. Notiziario S. I. M., 31 (2), 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="2013">Fasulo (2013)</bibRefCitation>
, who considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Bellini, 1904" authorityName="Bellini" authorityYear="1904" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Limnaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionida" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="truncatula" variety="neapolitana">
<emphasis box="[1066,1288,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Limnaea truncatula</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">neapolitana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[209,356,1053,1079]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="33 - 44" refId="ref15711" refString="Bellini, R. (1904 d) The freshwater shells of Naples and the neighbourhood. Journal of Conchology, 11 (2), 33 - 44." type="journal article" year="1904">Bellini, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Poli, 1791" authorityName="Poli" authorityYear="1791" box="[559,711,1053,1079]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Limnaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionida" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="truncatula">
<emphasis box="[559,711,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">G. truncatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This taxon was never figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[1101,1267,1053,1079]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="33 - 44" refId="ref15711" refString="Bellini, R. (1904 d) The freshwater shells of Naples and the neighbourhood. Journal of Conchology, 11 (2), 33 - 44." type="journal article" year="1904">Bellini (1904d</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[1280,1351,1053,1079]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="7 - 19" refId="ref15741" refString="Bellini, R. (1908 a) Etudes de Malacologie napolitaine. I. Les Mollusques terrestres et fluviatiles de la region volcanique (Vesuve et Champs Phlegrees). Annales de la Societe Royale Zoologique et Malacologique de Belgique, 42 (1), 7 - 19." type="journal article" year="1908">1908a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[1363,1423,1052,1079]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="149 - 194" refId="ref15792" refString="Bellini, R. (1915) I molluschi extramarini dei dintorni di Napoli. Monografia sintetica. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 2, 27, 149 - 194." type="journal article" year="1915">1915</bibRefCitation>
); however, taking into account the absence of congeneric and/or similar species from the Naples area (
<bibRefCitation author="Welter-Schultes, F." pageId="20" pageNumber="363" refId="ref19699" refString="Welter-Schultes, F. (2012) European non-marine molluscs, a guide for species identification. Planet Poster Editions, Gottingen, 680 pp." type="book" year="2012">Welter-Schultes 2012</bibRefCitation>
), as well as the fact that it is generally a very common species, we are prone to accept that it was truly described as based on 
<taxonomicName authority="Poli, 1791" authorityName="Poli" authorityYear="1791" box="[374,525,1161,1187]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Limnaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionida" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="truncatula">
<emphasis box="[374,525,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">G. truncatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This taxon was not found during samplings held in the area in the 1980’s (
<bibRefCitation author="Battaglini, P. &amp; Valentino, M. G." pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="233 - 259" refId="ref15554" refString="Battaglini, P. &amp; Valentino, M. G. (1981 - 1982) Aspetti ecologici di un fiume urbano ad alta alterazione ambientale (Fiume Sebeto). Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, 90 - 91, 233 - 259." type="book chapter" year="1981">
Battaglini &amp; Valentino 
<date box="[352,408,1197,1223]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" value="1981" valueMax="1982">1981</date>
</bibRefCitation>
–1982), and therefore it presumably did not survive the anthropogenic changes to which the Sebeto River has been subjected in the last century.
</paragraph>
